article.headline: BOISE ST 73, WISC MILWAUKEE 70
article.story:
NAMPA, Idaho (Ticker) -- Aaron Haynes scored 20 points as 
Boise State held off Wisconsin-Milwaukee, 73-70, in a
first-round National Invitation Tournament matchup.

The Broncos (23-9) play at Marquette in a second-round contest
on Tuesday.

Haynes scored 12 points in the first half to help Boise State
take a 44-32 advantage into the break.  The Broncos held a 71-67
lead after Haynes sank a pair of free throws with 45 seconds
left, but the Panthers pulled within 71-70 on a 3-pointer by Ed
McCants with 30 seconds to play.

After Coby Karl made two free throws to make it 73-70 with 15
seconds left, Wisconsin-Milwaukee's Chris Hill missed a layup
with three seconds remaining and Boise State held on.

Dylan Page had 23 points to pace the Panthers (20-11), the
Horizon League regular-season champions who were playing in the
NIT for the first time.
